Interface ILogicalVisitor<R,​P>

Type Parameters:
R - The type of the return value
P - The type of the input parameter
public interface ILogicalVisitor<R,​P>
The visitor to an ILogicalHost that has cases for the true and false states of the host. Note that the host is NOT passed to the cases when they are run because the host contains no information other than its state which is known by which case was called. The host's state is defined by the case it calls on its visitor. Any necessary information for the case can be passed in via the input parameter or whatever the visitor is closing over.
